        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 5:32PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 531 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Luna Pier, or 7 miles south of Monroe, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Monroe, Luna Pier, La Salle, Toledo Beach, Woodland Beach, Bolles
Harbor, and Detroit Beach.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
